:{\"standoff\":15},\"zerolinecolor\":\"white\",\"automargin\":true,\"zerolinewidth\":2},\"scene\":{\"xaxis\":{\"backgroundcolor\":\"#E5ECF6\",\"gridcolor\":\"white\",\"linecolor\":\"white\",\"showbackground\":true,\"ticks\":\"\",\"zerolinecolor\":\"white\",\"gridwidth\":2},\"yaxis\":{\"backgroundcolor\":\"#E5ECF6\",\"gridcolor\":\"white\",\"linecolor\":\"white\",\"showbackground\":true,\"ticks\":\"\",\"zerolinecolor\":\"white\",\"gridwidth\":2},\"zaxis\":{\"backgroundcolor\":\"#E5ECF6\",\"gridcolor\":\"white\",\"linecolor\":\"white\",\"showbackground\":true,\"ticks\":\"\",\"zerolinecolor\":\"white\",\"gridwidth\":2}},\"shapedefaults\":{\"line\":{\"color\":\"#2a3f5f\"}},\"annotationdefaults\":{\"arrowcolor\":\"#2a3f5f\",\"arrowhead\":0,\"arrowwidth\":1},\"geo\":{\"bgcolor\":\"white\",\"landcolor\":\"#E5ECF6\",\"subunitcolor\":\"white\",\"showland\":true,\"showlakes\":true,\"lakecolor\":\"white\"},\"title\":{\"x\":0.05},\"mapbox\":{\"style\":\"light\"},\"margin\":{\"b\":0,\"l\":0,\"r\":0,\"t\":30}}},\"xaxis\":{\"anchor\":\"y\",\"domain\":[0.0,1.0],\"title\":{\"text\":\"\"}},\"yaxis\":{\"anchor\":\"x\",\"domain\":[0.0,1.0],\"title\":{\"text\":\"Revenue (\\u20ac)\"},\"gridcolor\":\"#252535\"},\"legend\":{\"title\":{\"text\":\"Category\"},\"tracegroupgap\":0,\"bgcolor\":\"rgba(0,0,0,0)\"},\"title\":{\"text\":\"Revenue by Region and Category\",\"font\":{\"color\":\"#ffffff\"}},\"barmode\":\"group\",\"font\":{\"color\":\"#9898b0\"},\"plot_bgcolor\":\"#14141f\",\"paper_bgcolor\":\"#14141f\"},                        {\"responsive\": true}                    ).then(function(){\n                            \nvar gd = document.getElementById('d03a1d94-d8d7-4e5a-9d38-c0a4a108c269');\nvar x = new MutationObserver(function (mutations, observer) {{\n        var display = window.getComputedStyle(gd).display;\n        if (!display || display === 'none') {{\n            console.log([gd, 'removed!']);\n            Plotly.purge(gd);\n            observer.disconnect();\n        }}\n}});\n\n// Listen for the removal of the full notebook cells\nvar notebookContainer = gd.closest('#notebook-container');\nif (notebookContainer) {{\n    x.observe(notebookContainer, {childList: true});\n}}\n\n// Listen for the clearing of the current output cell\nvar outputEl = gd.closest('.output');\nif (outputEl) {{\n    x.observe(outputEl, {childList: true});\n}}\n\n                        })                };            </script>        </div>\n```\n\nRevenue split by region and category. Distribution is broadly even across Irish regions.\n:::\n:::\n\n\n---\n\n## Project Checklist\n\nProgress through this analysis:\n\n- [x] Load and inspect the dataset\n- [x] Check for nulls and data type issues\n- [x] Analyse monthly revenue trend\n- [x] Break down revenue by category\n- [x] Explore regional distribution\n- [ ] Build a predictive sales forecast (future work)\n\n---\n\n## Key Takeaways\n\n::: {.callout-note}\n## What this analysis found\n\n- Revenue follows a clear **seasonal arc** peaking in Q4 — promotional spend should be front-loaded into Q3 to capture the ramp-up.\n- **Electronics** generates disproportionate revenue relative to transaction count — protecting margin here matters more than volume discounts.\n- **Regional revenue is broadly distributed**, so a Dublin-only marketing focus would miss a substantial share of the market.\n:::\n\n::: {.callout-tip}\n## Next steps\nA natural follow-up is forecasting: does the Q4 peak come from higher basket sizes, or more transactions? That's the next query to write.\n:::\n\n---\n\n## Reflection\n\nThis project reinforced something I keep running into — the most useful output of an EDA isn't the visualisations themselves, it's the shortlist of questions they raise. Clean data still takes time, even when it's synthetic. There were real decisions to make about aggregation level, date formatting, and how to handle multi-category breakdowns without obscuring the signal.\n\n<br>\n[← Back to Projects](../index.qmd){.btn-ghost}